==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adminicle
<hw>Ad*min"i*cle</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>adminculum</ets> support, orig., that on which the hand rests;
<ets>ad</ets> + <ets>manus</ets> hand + dim. ending
<ets>-culym</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Help or support; an
auxiliary.</def> <rj><au>Grote.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Corroborative or explanatory
proof.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>In <xex>Scots law</xex>, any writing tending to establish the
existence or terms of a lost deed. <rj><au>Bell.</au></rj> </note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adminicular</ent>⟦br⟧
